{{About|the national park|the mountain range|Aladağlar}} {{Infobox protected area | name = Aladağlar National Park | alt_name = ''Aladağlar Milli Parkı'' | iucn_category = | photo = Aladağlar 01.JPG | photo_alt = | photo_caption = A view of Aladağlar. | photo_width = | map = Turkey | map_alt = | map_caption = | map_width = | relief = yes | label = Aladağlar NP | label_position = top | mark = | marker_size = | location = [[Yahyalı]], [[Kayseri Province]]-[[Çamardı]], [[Niğde Province]]-[[Aladağ, Adana|Aladağ]], [[Adana Province]], Turkey | nearest_city = | coordinates = {{coords|37|49|22.63|N|35|10|15.15|E|region:TR|display=inline, title}} | area = {{convert|55065|ha|abbr=on}} | designation = | authorized = | created = | established = {{start date|1995|04|21}} | designated = | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | visitation_ref = | governing_body = [[Ministry of Forest and Water Management (Turkey)|Ministry of Forest and Water Management]] | administrator = | operator = | owner = | world_heritage_site = | website = {{URL|http://www.milliparklar.gov.tr/mp/aladaglar/index.htm}} | child = | embedded = }} '''Aladağlar National Park''' ({{lang-tr|Aladağlar Milli Parkı}})), established on April 21, 1995, is a [[national park]] in southern Turkey. The national park, a mountain range of [[Anti-Taurus Mountains]] ({{lang-tr|Aladağlar}}), stretches over the locations [[Yahyalı]] in [[Kayseri Province]], [[Çamardı]] in [[Niğde Province]] and [[Aladağ, Adana|Aladağ]] in [[Adana Province]].<ref name="mp"/>
It covers an area of {{convert|55065|ha|abbr=on}} at an average elevation of {{convert|3500|m|ft|abbr=on}} above mean sea level.<ref name=mp/>
