==R==

{{glossary}}
<span id="rail gauge"></span>{{term|term='''[[rail gauge]]'''}}
{{defn|defn=The distance between the two rails of a railroad.<ref name="IIP 2008"/>}}

<span id="rainforest"></span>{{term|term='''[[rainforest]]'''}}
{{defn|defn=Any {{gli|forest}} characterized by abundant rainfall, dense layers of vegetation, and extremely high {{gli|biological diversity|biodiversity}}. Rainforests are found in both tropical and temperate regions. The term ''{{gli|jungle}}'' is sometimes used to refer to a tropical rainforest.}}

<span id="rainshadow"></span>{{term|term='''[[rainshadow]]'''}}
{{defn|defn=An area on the {{gli|leeward}} (downwind) side of a mountain or mountain range that receives greatly diminished precipitation.<ref name="IIP 2008"/>}}

<span id="ravine"></span>{{term|term='''[[ravine]]'''}}
