<span id="windward"></span>{{term|term='''[[windward]]'''}}
{{defn|defn=The side of a landmass facing the direction from which the wind is blowing. It is the opposite of {{gli|leeward}}.}}

<span id="World Geodetic System"></span>{{term|term='''[[World Geodetic System]] (WGS)'''}}
{{defn|defn=A standard {{gli|geographic coordinate system}}, spheroidal {{gli|reference ellipsoid}} (for raw {{gli|altitude}} data), and {{gli|geoid}} (which defines the nominal {{gli|sea level}}) used in {{gli|cartography}}, {{gli|geodesy}}, and {{gli|satellite navigation}} applications worldwide. The latest revision, ''WGS84'', is the standard coordinate system used by the {{gli|Global Positioning System}}.}}

<span id="world map"></span>{{term|term='''[[world map]]'''}}
{{defn|defn=A {{gli|map}} of most or all of the surface of the Earth.}}

