{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2013}}
{{Expand list|date=September 2016}}
This is a '''list of countries by age at first marriage'''.  Definition of marriage is the legally or formally recognized union of two people as partners in a personal relationship (historically and in some jurisdictions specifically a union between a man and a woman)<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://google.com/|title=Google|website=google.com|language=en|access-date=2018-04-10}}</ref>. Marriage is a legally recognized union between two partners in a relationship. The average age to first get married varies from one country to another and is affected by several factors such as financial stability, career, academic pursuit, and family background.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.worldatlas.com/articles/the-nations-of-europe-by-the-average-age-at-first-marriage.html|title=The Nations Of Europe By The Average Age At First Marriage|work=WorldAtlas|access-date=2018-04-10|language=en}}</ref> This list is current from the most recent surveys and does not treat the topic in history.

Because the [[Age Distribution|age distribution]] of people at first marriage is [[skewness|skewed]] with a longer tail towards older ages,<ref>Australian Bureau of Statistics [http://www.abs.gov.au/ausstats/abs@.nsf/2f762f95845417aeca25706c00834efa/a8d1bea8a2ff1b33ca2570ec001b0dc3!OpenDocument Family "Formation: Age at first marriage"]. 21 May 2011.</ref> the majority of people marry before the [[average]] age of first [[marriage]]. The [[median]] age is a more precise representation of when the majority of people marry,  however, for most reporting sources, only the average age at marriage is reported.

Some countries have most recent and updated [[census]] while other countries haven't been updated since the 1990s. 
