This is a '''[[list of countries]] ([[sovereign states]]) and territories without an airport'''.
==Countries (sovereign states)== Of the world's [[list of sovereign states|independent states]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://geography.about.com/cs/countries/a/numbercountries.htm |title=The Number of Countries in the World – Number of Countries Worldwide |publisher=Geography.About.com |date= |accessdate=2012-06-10}}</ref> only the five [[European microstates]] have no airport within their boundaries, though all have at least one [[heliport]]. All apart from Monaco are [[landlocked]], one of which, Liechtenstein, is [[double landlocked|doubly landlocked]].
{| class="wikitable" |- ! Country !! Notes |- | {{nowrap|{{flag|Andorra}}}} | Andorra does not have an airport,<ref>[https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/geos/an.html Andorra]. [[CIA World Factbook]]. Retrieved 2014-07-12.</ref> but does have three private heliports, one of which is a hospital helipad. A "National Heliport" is projected to be built, but the process is currently stalled.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.diariandorra.ad/noticies/editorial/2018/05/12/l_heliport_dubte_130344_1131.html |title=L'heliport, en dubte |publisher=Diari d'Andorra |date=2018-05-12 |accessdate=2018-07-28}}</ref> By both population and by land area, it is the largest country not to have an airport. The nearest airports in [[Spain]] are [[Andorra–La Seu d'Urgell Airport]] (12 km away), [[Lleida-Alguaire Airport]], [[Barcelona-El Prat Airport]], and [[Girona-Costa Brava Airport]]. The nearest airports in [[France]] are [[Carcassonne Airport]], [[Perpignan–Rivesaltes Airport]] and [[Toulouse-Blagnac Airport]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.yourandorra.com/airport |title=Andorra flight information and best airport for Andorra flights |publisher=YourAndorra.com |date=2008-10-05 |accessdate=2010-04-18}}</ref> |- | {{nowrap|{{flag|Liechtenstein}}}} | Liechtenstein does not have an airport, but does have a heliport in the southern town of [[Balzers]].<ref>{{cite web |author=Thomas Schmid |url=http://www.tsis.ch/heli/heliport/balzers.php |title=Heliport Balzers FL LSXB |publisher=Tsis.ch |date= |accessdate=2010-04-18}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Matthias Vogt |url=http://www.heli.li/sites/heliports-balzers-lsxb.php |title=Heliport Balzers LSXB |publisher=Heli.li |date= |accessdate=2010-04-18 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100218000000/http://www.heli.li/sites/heliports-balzers-lsxb.php |archivedate=2010-02-18 |df= }}</ref> The nearest international airports are [[St. Gallen-Altenrhein Airport]] in [[Switzerland]] and [[Friedrichshafen Airport]] in [[Germany]], which have few scheduled flights. The nearest major airport is [[Zurich Airport]] in [[Switzerland]], which has rail services to [[Buchs, St. Gallen|Buchs]] and [[Sargans]].<ref name=europeforvisitors>[http://europeforvisitors.com/switzaustria/articles/liechtenstein.htm Liechtenstein] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150908122740/http://europeforvisitors.com/switzaustria/articles/liechtenstein.htm |date=2015-09-08 }}. Europe for Visitors.</ref> From these towns, it is possible to catch a [[PostBus Switzerland|Postal Bus]]<ref name=europeforvisitors /> or a [[Feldkirch–Buchs railway|train]] to Liechtenstein. |- | {{nowrap|{{flag|Monaco}}}} | Monaco does not have an airport, but does have [[Monaco Heliport]] in the Monégasque district of [[Fontvieille, Monaco|Fontvieille]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.world-airport-codes.com/monaco/fontvieille-heliport-4843.html |title=Fontvieille Heliport Airport (MCM) Details – Monaco |publisher=World-Airport-Codes.com |date= |accessdate=2010-04-18}}</ref> The nearest airport is [[Nice Côte d'Azur Airport]] in [[France]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://insurance.essentialtravel.co.uk/tg-europe/france/monaco-getting-there.asp |title=Getting To Monaco |publisher=Insurance.EssentialTravel.co.uk |date= |accessdate=2010-04-18 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100324000000/http://insurance.essentialtravel.co.uk/tg-europe/france/monaco-getting-there.asp |archivedate=2010-03-24 |df= }}</ref> |- | {{nowrap|{{flag|San Marino}}}} | San Marino does not have an airport,<ref>[https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/geos/sm.html San Marino]. [[CIA World Factbook]]. Retrieved 2014-07-12.</ref>but does have one heliport in [[Borgo Maggiore]] and a small [[airfield]] in [[Torraccia]] with a {{convert|680|m|sing=on|abbr=off}} grass runway. The nearest airport is [[Rimini]]'s [[Federico Fellini Airport]] in [[Italy]]. |- | {{nowrap|{{flag|Vatican City}}}} | Vatican City does not have an airport, but does have [[Vatican City Heliport]] in the western corner, which is used for visiting heads and officials of the [[city-state]].<ref>[http://www.tiscali.co.uk/reference/encyclopaedia/countryfacts/vaticancitystate.html#Transport Vatican City] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20051222000000/http://www.tiscali.co.uk/reference/encyclopaedia/countryfacts/vaticancitystate.html |date=2005-12-22 }}. Tiscali. Retrieved 2006-11-27.</ref> It would be physically impossible to fit an airport into the {{convert|0.44|km2|sing=on|abbr=on}} land area of the [[Holy See]].<ref>[https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/geos/vt.html Holy See (Vatican City)]. [[CIA World Factbook]].</ref> The nearest airport is [[Rome Ciampino Airport]] in [[Italy]]. |}
==States with limited recognition== *[[Nagorno-Karabakh Republic]]. While there is an [[Stepanakert Airport|airport in Stepanakert]], this has seen no air traffic movements since 1992. *[[Sahrawi Arab Democratic Republic]] *[[South Ossetia]] *[[State of Palestine]]. While there are [[List_of_airports_in_the_Palestinian_territories|four airports within the Palestinian territories]], none have been operational since 2004. *[[Transnistria]]
==Non-self-governing territories==
Of the world's 17 [[United Nations list of Non-Self-Governing Territories|non-self-governing territories]], two have no airport within their boundaries: [[Tokelau]] and the [[Pitcairn Islands]]. Both are islands without land connection, so fairly long boat trips are the only transportation.
{| class="wikitable" |- ! Territory !! Sovereign State !! Notes |- | {{nowrap|{{flag|Tokelau}}}} | {{nowrap|{{flag|New Zealand}}}} | Tokelau<ref group="note">Tokelau is a territory of [[New Zealand]] in the southern [[Pacific Ocean]] consisting of the [[atoll]]s of [[Atafu]], [[Nukunonu]], and [[Fakaofo]]. A referendum held in 2006 and 2007 to change the status of the islands to one of [[associated state|free association]] with New Zealand did not meet the needed threshold for approval.</ref> does not have an airport, so boats are the only means of travel and transport.<ref>[https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/geos/tl.html Tokelau]. [[CIA World Factbook]]. Retrieved 2014-07-12.</ref> |- | {{nowrap|{{flag|Pitcairn Islands}}}} | {{nowrap|{{flag|United Kingdom}}}} | The Pitcairn Islands<ref group="note">Pitcairn Islands is a British Overseas Territory in the southern Pacific Ocean consisting of four islands: Pitcairn, [[Henderson Island (Pitcairn Islands)|Henderson]], [[Ducie Island|Ducie]], and [[Oeno Island|Oeno]].</ref> do not have an airport or seaport; the islanders rely on longboats to ferry people and goods between ship and shore through [[Bounty Bay]].<ref>[https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/geos/pc.html Pitcairn]. [[CIA World Factbook]]. Retrieved 2014-07-13.</ref> |}
