{{Multiple issues|{{primary sources|date=December 2012}}{{Notability|Geography|date=December 2012}} }} {{Infobox building |name= The Paterson Building |former_names= |alternate_names= |status=Complete |image= The Paterson Building.jpg |image_alt= |image_size= |caption= |location= |address= 653 [[Saginaw Trail|S. Saginaw St.]] |location_town= [[Flint, Michigan|Flint, MI]] 48502 |location_country= United States |coordinates = {{coord|43.0144|-83.6889|region:US-MI|display=inline,title}} |groundbreaking_date= |start_date= |completion_date=1931 |opened_date= |inauguration_date= |demolition_date= |destruction_date= |architect= |landlord= Thomas W. Collison & Co., Inc. Suite 307 |owner= |cost= |floor_area= |top_floor= |floor_count= |awards= |ren_awards= |parking= |references= |map_type= |map_alt= |map_caption= |altitude= |building_type= |architectural_style= |structural_system= |ren_cost= |client= |current_tenants= |renovation_date= |height= |architectural= |tip= |antenna_spire= |roof= |observatory= |other_dimensions= |seating_type= |seating_capacity= |elevator_count= |architecture_firm= |structural_engineer= |services_engineer= |civil_engineer= |other_designers= |quantity_surveyor= |main_contractor= |designations= |ren_architect= |ren_firm= |ren_str_engineer= |ren_serv_engineer= |ren_civ_engineer= |ren_oth_designers= |ren_qty_surveyor= |url= {{URL|http://thepatersonbuilding.com/}} }} [[File:Exterior Art Deco Terracotta.jpg|thumb|Exterior Art Deco Terracotta]] The '''Paterson Building''' is a historic office building located at 653 [[Saginaw Sting|South Saginaw Street]] and Third Street in Downtown [[Flint, Michigan]]. It was built by [[William A. Paterson]] of the [[Paterson (automobile)|Paterson Automotive Company]] in 1931,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.roadarch.com/deco/mi.html|title=Michigan Art Deco & Streamline Moderne Buildings {{!}} RoadsideArchitecture.com|website=www.roadarch.com|access-date=2017-06-18}}</ref> during the birth of the auto industry. The Paterson building has been owned by Thomas W. Collison Jr. of the Collison Family for close to 30 years. It has three beautiful floors with a full garage in the basement level. It provides heated valet parking for its tenants. The building consists of mainly law and medical offices. There are also retail stores on the Third Street side. Peace Barn is a vintage shop known for hand made flower crowns, vintage and shabby chic decor and vinyl records. The Beauty Box Boutique offers high end fashion and one of a kind hand made gifts. The building is rich in [[Art Deco]], which has been maintained throughout the interior and exterior of the building.{{cn|date=March 2013}}
