{{expand language|topic=|langcode=de|otherarticle=|date=July 2018}} {{italic title}} {{Infobox book | name = Vater telefoniert mit den Fliegen | author = [[Herta Müller]] | title_working = | illustrator = | language = German | subject = | genre = [[Poetry]], [[collage]] | set_in = | publisher = [[Carl Hanser Verlag]], Munich | pub_date = August 2012 | pages = 192 | isbn = 978-3-446-23857-2 | preceded_by = | followed_by = }} '''''Vater telefoniert mit den Fliegen''''' (''Father's on the Phone with the Flies'') is a collection of [[collage]] poems by [[Nobel Prize in Literature|Nobel Prize]]-winning writer [[Herta Müller]] first published in 2012.<ref name=Focus>{{cite web |title=Herta Müllers „Vater telefoniert mit den Fliegen“ |url=https://www.focus.de/kultur/buecher/literatur-herta-muellers-vater-telefoniert-mit-den-fliegen_aid_810374.html |website=Focus |accessdate=23 July 2018 |language=de |date=31 August 2012}}</ref> The 191 collages are divided between five sections.<ref name="SZ">{{cite news |last1=Ottschofski |first1=Edith |title=Vom „Herzkran“ und der „Heimat zum Quadrat“ |url=https://www.siebenbuerger.de/zeitung/artikel/kultur/12624-vom-herzkran-und-der-heimat-zum.html |accessdate=23 July 2018 |work=Siebenbürgischer Zeitung |date=23 September 2012}}</ref> As with most of Müller's work, one of the collection's underlying themes is political, stemming from her experience living under the dictatorship of [[Nicolae Ceaușescu]] in [[Socialist Republic of Romania|Communist Romania]].<ref name="FNP">{{cite news |title=Ein Telefonat mit den Fliegen |url=http://www.fnp.de/nachrichten/kultur/Ein-Telefonat-mit-den-Fliegen;art679,252957 |accessdate=23 July 2018 |work=Frankfurter Neue Presse |date=12 October 2012}}</ref>
A selection of 73 of the poems was published in English in 2018, translated by Thomas Cooper, alongside the German originals.<ref>{{cite web |title=Father's on the phone with the flies: a selection |url=https://library.ualberta.ca/catalog/8241756 |website=University of Alberta Libraries |accessdate=23 July 2018}}</ref>
